				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: EQ II<a name="18321"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 1 04 7:31 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>It will come out late in 2004. EQII will have a locked encounter system which prevents powerleveling and kill stealing. Once a group or single person beings an encounter with one or more mobs no one will be able to interfere unless the people or person fighting the mob unlocks the encounter. There will be 28 final classes 4 of which are artisans which gain experience by creating items. The bard class will be broken up into dirge and troubador. Because it is a MMORPG emphasis will be placed on grouping. However, there will be solo content included. Grouping will give much better exp and loot than soloing. There are two starting cities, Freeport and Quenyos (I don't know how to spell it). Freeport will be the evil city and Quenyos will be good. Each city will be huge, freeport is made up of 17 zones.
<br />

<br />
EQ II is taking what didn't work in EQ and fixing it.
<br />

<br />
For great information on EQ2 you can go to www.eqii.com
<br />

<br />
edit: The graphics are amazing, you can see the offical screenshots here:
<br />

<br />
http://everquest2.station.sony.com/media.jsp</span></td>
