			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: EQ II<a name="18557"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 2 04 4:53 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>edit: <b>They are not removing soloing.</b> There will be <b>a lot</b> of solo content build in. The reason for doing this is to eliminate class imbalances. It is near impossible to make all classes balanced in solo and group situations. The solution, make grouping the best experience so all classes are equal. People who do not have time to find a group will have no problem soloing. The will be able to advance there character but not as much as they could by grouping. A lot of people liked to solo in EQ because it was the best experience and loot but in EQII a lot of people will prefer to group because it offers the best experience and loot. EQII is a MMORPG, the most fun and best rewards will be in interacting with other players.
<br />

<br />
There will also be solo only quests and solo only mobs. Players will not longer be able to leech a quest (like the epic) from their guild. In EQII when you see someone with a good quest item you will know that they are skilled and hard to work hard for it.
<br />

<br />
Don't think of EQII as EQ minus soloing, becuase it will not be that.
<br />

<br />
Quote: One thing I've heard is if a group of 6 kills encounter X, then each of them gets the exact same experience as a solo person killing encounter X. 
<br />

<br />
Whoever told you that is wrong. First of all the monsters (yes monsters, there will be no more single pulling) that are killed by groups will be near impossible to solo. Soloing will take place at the entrance to dungeons and grouping will take place deeper in the dungeons. When a group kills something the experience is divided amoungst the members and then a bonus is added like in EQ. Grouping will not offer 6 times the experience as soloing, that would make soloing useless. But grouping will definitly have the best experience and loot. 
<br />
(end of edit)
<br />

<br />

<br />
SWG was made more by Lucas Arts than Sony so you don't have to worry about EQII being like SWG.
<br />

<br />
It is going to be very differen't from FFXI. They have very few things in common other than that they are both MMORPG.
<br />

<br />
I forgot to mention that EQII will have a raid limit of 24 people. This will be an improvement on the raiding system in EQ. The designers will be able to design raids for a set number of people. A raid limit of 24 people will create a need for strategy and require each person to play their part well. This is unlike in EQ where the way to win is to throw as many people at the mob as possible. Raids will be designed to take about half an hour. 
<br />

<br />
I also forgot to tell you guys that there will be no more camping in EQII. Most named and quest mobs will be instanced. However, this does not mean you can kill the same guy over and over again. There will be time flags to prevent this. Once you kill a certain boss mob you will not be able to for a set time.
<br />

<br />

<br />
<b>EQII is taking what didn't work in Everquest and fixing or replacing it. There will be no extreme twinking, camping spawn points for hours, kill stealing, painful corpse recoveries (there will still be a penalty for death), powerleveling, and unbalenced classes.</b>
<br />

<br />
The requirements for making EQII run well are high, 2Ghz processer, 1 gig of ram, and a 128 mb graphics card.</span></td>
